cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.DS 

This paper is about unbiased learning-to-rank models and their application to search engines. The most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which is focused on search engines and ranking algorithms. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel method for training unbiased models. The third sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper deals with natural language queries and documents. The fourth sub-category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), as the paper applies the method to eCommerce search data. The fifth sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for estimating click propensities.
